            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9,000,000,000 for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to support Earth Science, Planetary Science, Astrophysics, Heliophysics, and Biological and Physical Sciences\n* Restores agency-wide scientific stability and workforce certainty via a $1.75 billion (24%) increase over the FY2026 enacted level\n* Sustains progress on peer-reviewed National Academies Decadal Survey priorities and long-term mission roadmaps",
            "rationale": "This value reflects the standard funding ask and account description provided in the reference values, including the specific FY2026 enacted comparison.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
