            "label": "Justification for program request",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Supports local innovation at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte, which received nearly $600,000 in recent NASA grants\n* Direct community benefit via Charlotte-based research connecting NASA Earth science data to local environmental justice initiatives\n* Protects U.S. global leadership and norm-setting in space against rapid expansion of Chinese space science capabilities\n* High economic efficiency: NASA investment returns roughly $3 to the economy for every $1 spent while strengthening the district's STEM pipeline",
            "rationale": "Justification leverages local spending data for UNC Charlotte, including the specific environmental justice project which aligns with the Member's district profile, combined with strategic advocacy points regarding China and economic ROI.",
            "confidence": "high"
